# SunnyFit AI Coding Agent Rules

You are an expert Frontend Developer building the SunnyFit Mobile App. 
You must strictly follow the Design System and Architectural constraints defined below.

## 1. Design System & UI Tokens (Mandatory)
When generating HTML, React, or Tailwind code, you must strictly use these extracted Figma values:

### Colors (Warmth & Companionship Theme)
* Brand Blue: `#2D4183` (Use for main navigation, primary backgrounds)
* Brand Red: `#EE4343` (Use for primary CTAs, emphasis)
* Page Background: `#FFFBF7` (Warm beige/off-white. MUST use this for the main app background instead of cold grays/blues)
* Card Background: `#FFFFFF` (Pure white for floating cards/modals)
* Text: Use `#000000` with opacity (e.g., `text-black/90` for primary, `text-black/60` for secondary)
* Functional: Success `#34C759`, Error `#FF3B30`, Warning `#FF9500`

### Typography (Converted to actual 1X development sizes)
* Font Family: `Montserrat` (Primary), fallback to `system-ui`
* Display: `32px`, leading `44.8px`, font-weight `600`
* H1: `20px`, leading `24px`, font-weight `400`
* H2: `16px`, leading `24px`, font-weight `900`
* H3: `14px`, leading `20px`, font-weight `700`
* Body/Text: `14px`, leading `22px`, font-weight `400`
* Caption/Small: `12px`, leading `16px`

### Layout & Sizing
* Container: All pages must be constrained within a mobile viewport of `width: 390px; height: 844px;`.
* Grid: 4 columns, 16px margins, 16px gaps.
* Cards/Modals: Border radius MUST be `20px`.
* Buttons: Primary buttons height `56px` (or standard 40px/32px variants), border radius `16px`.

### Iconography & Assets
* Icons: When you need UI icons, assume they exist in a global `Icons` object (e.g., `<Icons.ChevronLeft />`, `<Icons.Check />`) or use inline SVGs that match a clean, rounded, warm style. 

## 2. SOP 3.2 Data Tracking & Interaction (Mandatory)
To maintain dual-binding with the PRD markdown:
* EVERY interactive element (button, card, toggle, etc.) MUST have a `data-zone-id` attribute.
* The naming convention for `data-zone-id` is `[module]_[page]_[action]`.
* DO NOT use generic `<a>` tags for routing. Use `window.parent.postMessage({ type: 'ZONE_CLICK', zoneId: '...' }, '*');` to emit events to the PRD viewer shell.

## 3. General Output Rules
* Write clean, semantic HTML5 / React.
* Use Tailwind CSS for styling exclusively.
* Prioritize modern, flat, and warm design aesthetics. No heavy drop-shadows unless it's the primary floating CTA (`shadow-float-btn`).